==English==

===Noun===
'''[[nerf]] [[ball]]''' &trade;

# (''Trademark owned by Hasbro corporation'') Any small [[foam]] [[ball]], soft and very light, designed for indoor use.
#: ''Getting hit by a Nerf® ball doesn't hurt at all.''
#: ''This mini''' nerf ball''' whistles when thrown hard and flies really well. Unlike its bigger brother, this Vortex '''Nerf ball''' is much softer and lighter, perfect for kids'' [http://www.firetoys.co.uk/juggling/Pocket_Nerf_howler.html]
====Usage notes====
Like many trademarked terms, this term is also used generically in common speech.  However, Hasbro would prefer that it always be capitalized in written text, and a trademark notice added.

